# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the dollar firmed on wednesday against other major currencies on the london forex market , while sterling slipped ahead of british local elections on thursday that may well weaken the british government 's position , forex dealers said in late afternoon .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (d / deal-01
                  :ARG2 (f / forex)))
      :ARG1 (c / contrast-01
            :ARG1 (f2 / firmed-01
                  :ARG1 (d2 / dollar)
                  :ARG3 (c2 / currency
                        :mod (o / other)
                        :ARG1-of (m / major-02))
                  :time (d3 / date-entity
                        :weekday (w / wednesday))
                  :location (m2 / market
                        :mod (f3 / forex)
                        :location (c3 / city
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "London"))))
            :ARG2 (s2 / slip-01
                  :ARG1 (p2 / pound)
                  :time (a / ahead
                        :op1 (e / elect-01
                              :ARG1-of (l / local-02)
                              :location (c4 / country
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Britain"))
                              :time (d4 / date-entity
                                    :weekday (t / thursday))
                              :ARG0-of (w2 / weaken-01
                                    :ARG1 (p3 / position-02
                                          :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                                                :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                                                      :ARG1 c4)))
                                    :ARG1-of (p4 / possible-01)
                                    :mod (w3 / well)))))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a veteran ##-year-old australian pilot was plucked from the waters of the south pacific tuesday after crashing a small plane in the middle of the ocean for the second time in four years .
# ::alignments
(p / pluck-01
      :ARG1 (p2 / person
            :ARG0-of (p3 / pilot-01)
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Australia"))
            :age (t / temporal-quantity
                  :quant 1
                  :unit (y / year))
            :mod (v / veteran))
      :ARG2 (w / water
            :location (c2 / country-region
                  :name n
                  :op1 "South"
                  :op2 "Pacific"))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday))
      :time (a / after
            :op1 (c3 / crash-01
                  :ARG0 p2
                  :ARG1 (p4 / plane
                        :mod (s / small))
                  :location (m / middle
                        :part-of (o / ocean))
                  :ord (o2 / ordinal-entity
                        :value 2
                        :range (t3 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 4
                              :unit (y2 / year))))))

# ::id 1920 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok u.s. middle east peace coordinator dennis ross will arrive here tuesday for talks with egyptian foreign minister amr moussa on the stalled mideast peace process .
# ::alignments
(a / arrive-01
      :ARG1 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Dennis"
                  :op2 "Ross")
            :ARG0-of (c / coordinate-01
                  :ARG1 (p2 / peace))
            :mod (c2 / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "U.S.")))
      :ARG4 (h / here)
      :purpose (t / talk-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (p3 / process-02
                  :ARG1 (p4 / peace)
                  :ARG1-of (s / stall-01)
                  :location (w / world-region
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Mideast")))
            :ARG2 (p5 / person
                  :name (n4 / name
                        :op1 "Amr"
                        :op2 "Moussa")
                  :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (c3 / country
                              :name (n5 / name
                                    :op1 "Egypt"))
                        :ARG2 (m / minister
                              :topic (f / foreign)))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday)))
